text.section:
Before a certificate of qualification expires, the holder periodically may renew it for an additional 2-year term, if the holder:
otherwise is entitled to a certificate of qualification;
submits to the Commissioner a renewal application on the form that the Commissioner provides;
pays to the Commissioner the renewal fee required by § 2-112 of this article; and
complies with the bond requirement of § 3-313 of this subtitle.
